40|$|A {{family of}} {{bell-shaped}} distributions {{built around the}} hyperbolic secant is devised. Moment and <b>cumulant</b> <b>generating</b> <b>functions</b> are provided leading to closed form representations of moments in terms of polygamma functions. As a by-product the behaviour of kurtosis is investigated showing that it is upperly bounded by six and lowerly bounded by three. The distributions at stake bridge the Laplace and Gaussian laws, both arising as limit distributions...|$|R
40|$|Using {{diagrammatic}} techniques, {{we provide}} explicit functional {{relations between the}} <b>cumulant</b> <b>generating</b> <b>functions</b> for the biunitarily invariant ensembles {{in the limit of}} large size of matrices. The formalism allows to map two distinct areas of free random variables: Hermitian positive definite operators and non-normal R-diagonal operators. We also rederive the Haagerup-Larsen theorem and show how its recent extension to the eigenvector correlation function appears naturally within this approach. Comment: 18 pages, 6 figures, version accepted for publicatio...|$|R
