40|$|This paper {{provides}} a unified and comprehensive {{approach that is}} useful in deriving expressions for higher order cumulants of random vectors. The use of this methodology is then illustrated in three diverse and novel contexts, namely: (i) in obtaining a lower bound (Bhattacharya bound) for the variance- covariance matrix of a vector of unbiased estimators where the density depends on several parameters, (ii) in studying the asymptotic theory of multivariable statistics when the population is not necessarily Gaussian and finally, (iii) {{in the study of}} multivariate nonlinear time series models and in obtaining higher order cumulant spectra. The approach depends on expanding the characteristic <b>functions</b> and <b>cumulant</b> <b>generating</b> <b>functions</b> in terms of the Kronecker products of di¤erential operators. Our objective here is to derive such expressions using only elementary calculus of several variables and also to highlight some important applications in statistics...|$|R
